<frame name="FR_Becoming_aware" ID="10086" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Cognitive_positions">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;Words in this frame have to do with a &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; adding some &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt; to their model of the world. They are similar to &lt;frframe&gt;Coming_to_believe&lt;/frframe&gt; words, except the latter generally involve reasoning from Evidence. Even though some Evidence may be present in context, this frame's LUs do not allow for it to be locally expressed. FR_Becoming_aware includes LUs that may subcategorize an entity-type object, and are thus ambiguous with the Perception_active or the Perception_experience frames, but it also includes LUs that only allow for a state_of_affairs  &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt;.
    &lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;asf&gt;Relation to fndata-1.5&lt;/asf&gt; : slight modification of Becoming_aware : the Means FE is not considered as Core, neither is it annotated since no LU of this frame subcategorizes it. The difference with Coming_to_believe is explicitly the coreness of the Evidence role: Coming_to_believe's LUs all necessarily include some sort of evidence that the new belief is based on.


&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Distinctions with other frames:&lt;/asf&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

≠ &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Cognizer_affecting.veracity&lt;/frframe&gt;: FR_Becoming_aware's LUs do not imply that the Cognizer's stance on the Content was based on anything, whereas Coming_to_believe's LUs imply that either a person or a situation initiated the Cognizer's stance.

    &lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

≠ &lt;frframe&gt;Coming_to_believe&lt;/frframe&gt;: Evidence is only a core role for Coming_to_believe: FR_Becoming_aware's LUs do not imply that the Cognizer's stance on the Content was based on anything, whereas Coming_to_believe's do.


&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:52 PST Wed" abbrev="Cog" name="Cognizer" ID="87">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; is the person who becomes aware of a &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt;. It is normally expressed as an External Argument.

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Cog"&gt;Pat&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;discovered&lt;/t&gt; he had already gone.&lt;/ex&gt; &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:52 PST Wed" abbrev="Phen" name="Phenomenon" ID="88">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;Thm &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt; is the entity or situation in the world of which a &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; becomes aware. 

&lt;ex&gt;Pat &lt;t&gt;discovered&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Phenomenon"&gt;she had already left&lt;/fex&gt; in Soho.&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="006400" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Peripheral" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:53 PST Wed" abbrev="Evid" name="Evidence" ID="91">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Evidence&lt;/fen&gt; is some fact that allows the &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; to become aware of something.

&lt;ex&gt;We &lt;t&gt;discovered&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Evidence"&gt;from their job performance&lt;/fex&gt; that they were well-trained.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="800080" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="664" cDate="06/22/2001 08:17:59 PDT Fri" abbrev="Top" name="Topic" ID="963">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;&lt;fen&gt;Topic&lt;/fen&gt; indicates the general field within which the &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt; is found.

&lt;ex&gt;Scientists attempt to make &lt;t&gt;discoveries&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Top"&gt;about the laws of nature&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
        <FE bgColor="808080" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="618" cDate="08/16/2005 02:39:34 PDT Tue" abbrev="ins" name="Instrument" ID="8876">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; uses an &lt;fen&gt;Instrument&lt;/fen&gt; to (enable themselves to) become aware of the &lt;fen&gt;Phenomenon&lt;/fen&gt;.  In some cases, the &lt;fen&gt;Instrument&lt;/fen&gt; may appear in subject position.

&lt;ex&gt;Olson says the deputy came out to the farm and &lt;t&gt;detected&lt;/t&gt; a radioactive substance &lt;fex name="ins"&gt;with his Geiger counter&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
